00:37:20,989 --> 00:37:22,657
If it is passed,

726
00:37:23,534 --> 00:37:25,034
but it shall not pass!

727
00:37:30,833 --> 00:37:31,791
What's more interesting

728
00:37:31,875 --> 00:37:32,875
is how dismal and disgruntled

729
00:37:33,001 --> 00:37:34,335
Mr. Yeaman appears.

730
00:37:35,504 --> 00:37:37,338
Every member of this House...

731
00:37:37,548 --> 00:37:38,714
He should be cheering right now.

732
00:37:38,841 --> 00:37:40,341
Looks like he ate a bad oyster.

733
00:37:40,426 --> 00:37:42,593
...Party and
the constituents it serves

734
00:37:42,678 --> 00:37:43,845
shall oppose...

735
00:37:44,555 --> 00:37:47,306
Point of order,
Mr. Speaker, if you please.

736
00:37:47,391 --> 00:37:49,142
Mr. Speaker, I still have the floor.

737
00:37:49,226 --> 00:37:50,309
And the gentleman from Pennsylvania

738
00:37:50,394 --> 00:37:51,644
is out of order!

739
00:37:51,728 --> 00:37:53,604
When will Mr. Wood conclude
his interminable gabble?

740
00:37:53,689 --> 00:37:55,857
Some of us breathe oxygen

741
00:37:56,358 --> 00:37:59,152
and we find the mephitic
fumes of his oratory

742
00:37:59,236 --> 00:38:02,530
a lethal challenge
to our pulmonary capabilities!

743
00:38:05,742 --> 00:38:08,202
We shall oppose this amendment,

744
00:38:08,287 --> 00:38:10,872
and any legislation that
